article.headline: Alabama 85, Georgia St 58
article.story: TUSCALOOSA, Ala. (AP) -- Chuck Davis scored 22 points and Alonzo Gee added 19 to lead Alabama to a 85-58 rout of Georgia State on Saturday. Davis, who shot 9-of-13 from the field, helped the Crimson Tide (5-3) take its largest lead at 83-54 on a layup and free throw with 1:59 remaining in the game. Alabama, which led 49-37 at halftime, opened the second half with a 10-2 run. Boyd Copeland led the Panthers (2-5) with 14 points and Malcolm Manier added 10. Even though Georgia State shot 8-of-9 first half 3-pointers, it wasn't enough to offset the Tide's 11-of-13 free throw shooting. Alabama held Georgia State to 35 percent shooting, while still hitting 47 percent from the field. The Tide also had a rebound advantage of 43-27.
